# Load the data from the newly uploaded file
file_path = '/Users/helgegeurtjacobusmoes/Desktop/thesis data/Updated_Data_And_Topics.xlsx'
data = pd.read_excel(file_path)

# Check the number of rows in the dataset
total_rows = data.shape[0]

# Function to extract the year using regex
def extract_year_regex(date_str):
    match = re.search(r'\b(19|20)\d{2}\b', date_str)
    if match:
        return int(match.group(0))
    return pd.NaT

# Ensure all publication dates are treated as strings
data['Publication Date'] = data['Publication Date'].astype(str)

# Apply the regex function to the 'Publication Date' column
data['Publication Year'] = data['Publication Date'].apply(extract_year_regex)

# Check for any missing values in the 'Topic' and 'Publication Year' columns
missing_topic = data['Topic'].isna().sum()
missing_year = data['Publication Year'].isna().sum()

# Group by 'Topic' and 'Publication Year' and count the number of articles
articles_per_topic_year = data.groupby(['Topic', 'Publication Year']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)

# Add the total for each year
articles_per_topic_year.loc['Total'] = articles_per_topic_year.sum()

# Calculate the total number of articles for each year
year_totals = articles_per_topic_year.loc['Total']

# Calculate the percentage of articles for each year
percentages_per_year = (articles_per_topic_year.div(year_totals, axis=1) * 100).round(1)

# Combine the counts and percentages into one table
combined_table_with_totals = pd.concat([articles_per_topic_year, percentages_per_year], 
                                       keys=['Count', 'Percentage'], 
                                       axis=1)

# Verify the total count from the table matches the total number of rows
total_count_from_table = articles_per_topic_year.sum().sum()

total_rows, missing_topic, missing_year, total_count_from_table

# Ensure all publication dates are treated as strings
data['Publication Date'] = data['Publication Date'].astype(str)

# Function to extract the year using regex
def extract_year_regex(date_str):
    match = re.search(r'\b(19|20)\d{2}\b', date_str)
    if match:
        return int(match.group(0))
    return pd.NaT

# Apply the regex function to the 'Publication Date' column
data['Publication Year'] = data['Publication Date'].apply(extract_year_regex)

# Handle missing publication years by labeling them as 'Unknown Year'
data['Publication Year'] = data['Publication Year'].fillna('Unknown Year')

# Group the data by year and topic name
topic_data_named = data.groupby(['Publication Year', 'Topic Name']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)

# Calculate the total number of articles per year
total_articles_per_year = topic_data_named.sum(axis=1)

# Calculate the percentage of articles per topic per year
percentage_data_named = topic_data_named.div(total_articles_per_year, axis=0) * 100

# Convert the index to strings to avoid '.0' in labels
topic_data_named.index = topic_data_named.index.astype(str)
percentage_data_named.index = percentage_data_named.index.astype(str)

# Prepare frequency and percentage data for merging
frequency_data_named = topic_data_named.stack().reset_index(name='Frequency')
percentage_data_named = percentage_data_named.stack().reset_index(name='Percentage')

# Merge frequency and percentage data
merged_data = pd.merge(frequency_data_named, percentage_data_named, on=['Publication Year', 'Topic Name'])

# Pivot to get the desired format
frequency_pivot = merged_data.pivot(index='Publication Year', columns='Topic Name', values='Frequency').fillna(0).astype(int)
percentage_pivot = merged_data.pivot(index='Publication Year', columns='Topic Name', values='Percentage').fillna(0).round(1)

# Combine frequency and percentage into one DataFrame with multi-level columns
total_combined_data = pd.concat([frequency_pivot.add_suffix('_Frequency'), percentage_pivot.add_suffix('_Percentage')], axis=1)

# Display the final combined data
total_combined_data

import pandas as pd

# Load the data from the provided Excel file
file_path = '/Users/helgegeurtjacobusmoes/Desktop/thesis data/Updated_Data_And_Topics.xlsx'
data = pd.read_excel(file_path, sheet_name='Sheet1')

# Convert 'Publication Date' to datetime with specified format
data['Publication Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Publication Date'], format='%d-%m-%Y', errors='coerce')
data['Year'] = data['Publication Date'].dt.year

# Drop rows where 'Topic Name' is missing
data = data.dropna(subset=['Topic Name'])

# Exclude rows with unknown year and "AI in Society" topic
data = data.dropna(subset=['Year'])
data = data[data['Topic Name'] != 'AI in Society']

# Group the data by year and topic name
topic_data_named = data.groupby(['Year', 'Topic Name']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)

# Calculate the total number of articles per year
total_articles_per_year = topic_data_named.sum(axis=1)

# Calculate the percentage of articles per topic per year
percentage_data_named = topic_data_named.div(total_articles_per_year, axis=0) * 100

# Convert the index to integers to avoid '.0' in labels
percentage_data_named.index = percentage_data_named.index.astype(int)
topic_data_named.index = topic_data_named.index.astype(int)

# Prepare frequency and percentage data for merging
frequency_data_named = topic_data_named.stack().reset_index(name='Frequency')
percentage_data_named = percentage_data_named.stack().reset_index(name='Percentage')

# Merge frequency and percentage data
merged_data = pd.merge(frequency_data_named, percentage_data_named, on=['Year', 'Topic Name'])

# Pivot to get the desired format
frequency_pivot = merged_data.pivot(index='Year', columns='Topic Name', values='Frequency').fillna(0).astype(int)
percentage_pivot = merged_data.pivot(index='Year', columns='Topic Name', values='Percentage').fillna(0).round(1)

# Combine frequency and percentage into one DataFrame with multi-level columns
combined_data = pd.concat([frequency_pivot.add_suffix('_Frequency'), percentage_pivot.add_suffix('_Percentage')], axis=1)

# Ensure frequency columns are integers and percentages have one decimal place
frequency_columns = [col for col in combined_data.columns if '_Frequency' in col]
percentage_columns = [col for col in combined_data.columns if '_Percentage' in col]

combined_data[frequency_columns] = combined_data[frequency_columns].astype('Int64')
combined_data[percentage_columns] = combined_data[percentage_columns].astype(float).round(1)

# Ensure percentages add up to 100% for each year
for year in combined_data.index:
    total_percentage = combined_data.loc[year, percentage_columns].sum()
    if total_percentage != 100:
        adjustment_factor = 100 / total_percentage
        combined_data.loc[year, percentage_columns] = combined_data.loc[year, percentage_columns] * adjustment_factor
        combined_data[percentage_columns] = combined_data[percentage_columns].round(1)

# Display the final combined data
combined_data

# Load the data from the provided Excel file
file_path = '/Users/helgegeurtjacobusmoes/Desktop/thesis data/Updated_Data_And_Topics.xlsx'
data = pd.read_excel(file_path, sheet_name='Sheet1')

# Convert 'Publication Date' to datetime with specified format
data['Publication Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Publication Date'], format='%d-%m-%Y', errors='coerce')
data['Year'] = data['Publication Date'].dt.year

# Drop rows where 'Topic Name' is missing
data = data.dropna(subset=['Topic Name'])

# Exclude the "AI in Society" topic
data = data[data['Topic Name'] != 'AI in Society']

# Group the data by year and topic name
topic_data_named = data.groupby(['Year', 'Topic Name']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)

# Convert the index to integers to avoid '.0' in labels
topic_data_named.index = topic_data_named.index.astype(int)

# Plot the number of articles on AI by year and topic name
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 7))
ax = topic_data_named.plot(kind='line', marker='o', ax=plt.gca())
ax.set_title('Number of Articles on AI by Year and Topic', fontsize=16)
ax.set_xlabel('Year', fontsize=14)
ax.set_ylabel('Number of Articles', fontsize=14)
ax.legend(title='Topic', fontsize=12)
plt.xticks(rotation=0, fontsize=12)
plt.yticks(fontsize=12)

# Set the x-ticks to display each year
years = topic_data_named.index
plt.xticks(ticks=years, labels=years, fontsize=12)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load the data from the provided Excel file
file_path = '/Users/helgegeurtjacobusmoes/Desktop/thesis data/Merged_Official_Thesis_Coding.xlsx'
data = pd.read_excel(file_path, sheet_name='Sheet1')

# Add the 'Year' column
data['Publication Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Publication Date'], dayfirst=True, errors='coerce')
data['Year'] = data['Publication Date'].dt.year

# Drop rows where the 'Publication Date' could not be parsed
data = data.dropna(subset=['Year'])

# Group by year and calculate the mean values for 'Updated AI Act' and 'Updated Risk'
data_grouped = data.groupby('Year')[['Updated AI Act', 'Updated Risk']].mean().reset_index()

# Plot the data
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 7))
plt.plot(data_grouped['Year'], data_grouped['Updated AI Act'], marker='o', label='AI Act')
plt.plot(data_grouped['Year'], data_grouped['Updated Risk'], marker='o', label='Risk')
plt.xlabel('Year', fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel('Mean Value', fontsize=14)
plt.title('AI Act and Risk Over the Years', fontsize=16)
plt.xticks(rotation=0, fontsize=12)
plt.yticks(fontsize=12)

# Set the x-ticks to display each year
years = data_grouped['Year']
plt.xticks(ticks=years, labels=years, fontsize=12)

# Add legend with title 'Variable'
plt.legend(title='Variable')
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
